courses.subject: Choose One
courses.customDesc:
Choose one of the following: ANT201, GEOG150, or Lower-Division Social Sciences Course.

Courses from the following disciplines will be acceptable towards the lower-division Social Sciences course: Anthropology, Ethnic Studies, Geography, Sociology, Political Science, Psychology, or Women's, Gender, and Queer Studies.

courses.subject: GE
courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, Upper-Division B, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, Upper-Division D, Lower-Division E, F, and GE Elective. Upper-Division B, Upper-Division C, and Upper-Division D should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Refer to online catalog for GE course selection and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR).

courses.subject: Applications & Issues Courses
courses.customDesc:
Any Applications & Issues course can go here.

Select from the following Applications and Issues courses: POLS245, POLS344; PSY352, PSY375, PSY460; SOC301, SOC395, SOC414, SOC440, SOC444. (Note: SOC440 can only be taken for 12 units max within concentration.) Consultation with faculty advisor is recommended.
